cs.CY, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper addresses a societal issue (Charge Point Anxiety) related to the adoption of electric vehicles, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The design and implementation of the dockChain adapter involves hardware components and charging policies, which are related to control systems and can be considered as a system-level solution.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper presents a distributed algorithm for detecting the length of the chain in a dockChain network, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The dockChain adapter enables multiple EVs to connect simultaneously to a single charge, which involves networking and internet architecture.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The distributed algorithm presented in the paper involves data structures and algorithms for detecting the length of the chain in a dockChain network.
